#: _posts/2025-11-27-mmaler-blogpost-2-quarkus-runtime-and-framework-for-cloud-native-java.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This post explores how Quarkus speeds up development, cuts costs, and "
"streamlines cloud-native Java."
msgstr "这篇文章将探讨 Quarkus 如何加快开发速度、降低成本并简化云原生 Java。"

#: _posts/2025-11-27-mmaler-blogpost-2-quarkus-runtime-and-framework-for-cloud-native-java.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Public clouds such as AWS, Microsoft Azure, and Google Cloud, and platforms "
"like Red Hat OpenShift, favor services that start fast and stay lean.\n"
"Quarkus is engineered for exactly that.\n"
"Build time processing reduces runtime overhead and results in rapid startup, "
"a small memory footprint, and frictionless deployment across Kubernetes, "
"OpenShift, serverless, and managed container services in any cloud.\n"
"If your Java services need to start in milliseconds, run dense on shared "
"nodes, and still feel great to build, Quarkus was made for that job."
msgstr ""
"AWS、Microsoft Azure 和 Google Cloud 等公有云以及 Red Hat OpenShift "
"等平台都青睐于快速启动并保持精简的服务。Quarkus正是为此而设计的。构建时间处理减少了运行时开销，从而实现了快速启动、内存占用小以及在任何云中跨 "
"Kubernetes、OpenShift、无服务器和托管容器服务的无缝部署。如果您的 Java "
"服务需要在毫秒级的时间内启动，在共享节点上密集运行，并且在构建时仍然感觉良好，那么 Quarkus 就是您的理想选择。"

#: _posts/2025-11-27-mmaler-blogpost-2-quarkus-runtime-and-framework-for-cloud-native-java.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Quarkus is a Java runtime that seamlessly integrates popular frameworks and "
"libraries, shaping both the structure of modern applications and the "
"developer experience behind them.\n"
"In this post, “runtime” means the full execution stack in production: JVM or "
"native, plus Quarkus and the integrated frameworks."
msgstr ""
"Quarkus 是一种 Java 运行时，可无缝集成流行的框架和库，塑造现代应用程序的结构及其背后的开发人员体验。在这篇文章中，\"运行时 "
"\"指的是生产中的整个执行堆栈：JVM 或本地，加上 Quarkus 和集成框架。"

#: _posts/2025-11-27-mmaler-blogpost-2-quarkus-runtime-and-framework-for-cloud-native-java.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Quarkus itself can also work as a framework, as it constitutes a higher-"
"level layer that provides structure and APIs."
msgstr "Quarkus 本身也可以作为一个框架，因为它构成了一个提供结构和应用程序接口的高层。"

